"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/659472","HM Treasury","false","2016-12-20","<p>On 8 November the Financial Conduct Authority (FCA) published a summary of the main findings from the skilled persons’ report it commissioned to review RBS’ treatment of SME customers transferred into its Global Restructuring Group. The FCA has said it is carefully considering the report and will publish a full account of their findings when practicable. It would not be appropriate for the government to comment further whilst this process is ongoing.</p>","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby",,"2016-12-20T14:14:11.167Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/659472/answer","Biography information for Simon Kirby","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/659472/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/659472/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-12-15","Royal Bank of Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, when he expects the Financial Conduct Authority report on the Global Restructuring Group of RBS to be published.","false","Biography information for Nigel Adams","Selby and Ainsty","Nigel Adams","57835"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/659473","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-12-22","<p>Under the business rates retention system, where a local authority uses its discretionary powers to grant business rates discounts the resulting loss of business rates income is effectively shared equally between the local authority and the Government. The Government does not collect data on particular types of premises that have benefited from local discretionary relief.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2016-12-22T16:00:45.33Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/659473/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/659473/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/659473/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-12-15","Nurseries: Non-domestic Rates","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, pursuant to the Answer of 21 October 2016 to Question 49076, if he will publish the amount that the Government has paid to each local authority in England to offer business rates reductions for childcare providers.","false","Biography information for Tulip Siddiq","Hampstead and Kilburn","Tulip Siddiq","57848"
